
@startuml

class Department {
  +String id
  +String name
  -List<Room> rooms
}

class Room {
  +String id
  +String name
  -List<Bed> beds
}

class Bed {
  +String id
  +String category
  -Category category
}

class Category {
  +String id
  +String name
  +double price
  -List<Stay> stays
}

class Inhabitant {
  +String id
  +String name
  +Date dateOfBirth
  +String contactInfo
  -List<Stay> stays
  -List<WaitingListEntry> waitingListEntries
}

class Stay {
  +String id
  +Date startDate
  +Date endDate
  +Category category
  -Department department
  -Room room
  -Bed bed
  -List<Invoice> invoices
}

class WaitingListEntry {
  +int position
  +Date registrationDate
  +Category category
  -Inhabitant inhabitant
}

class Invoice {
  +String id
  +Date invoiceDate
  +double totalAmount
  +double paidAmount
  +double outstandingAmount
  -List<Payment> payments
  -Stay stay
}

class Payment {
  +String id
  +Date paymentDate
  +double amount
  -Invoice invoice
}

class Proposal {
  +Date proposalDate
  +Category category
  -Inhabitant inhabitant
  -WaitingListEntry waitingListEntry
  +boolean accepted
}

class Assessment {
  +Date assessmentDate
  +Category recommendedCategory
  -Inhabitant inhabitant
}

@enduml

---

### ✅ Summary of Key Relationships:

- **Department** contains multiple **Rooms**.
- **Room** contains multiple **Beds**.
- **Bed** belongs to a **Category**.
- **Category** defines the type of stay (RH, RNH, SF) and has a **price**.
- **Inhabitant** can have multiple **Stays** (e.g., suspended or active).
- **Inhabitant** may be on a **WaitingListEntry** for a specific **Category**.
- A **Stay** generates one or more **Invoices**.
- **Invoice** can have multiple **Payments**.
- A **Proposal** is made to an **Inhabitant** from a **WaitingListEntry**.
- **Assessment** determines the **recommendedCategory** for an **Inhabitant**.

---

### 📌 Notes:
- The diagram assumes that some relationships are **aggregations** (e.g., `Department` contains `Room`) and others are **associations** (e.g., `Inhabitant` has `Stay`).

